<p>The most fun is from putting hashes in hashes:</p>

<pre>
my %one_user = (email => 'reuven@lerner.co.il',
		phone => '08-973-2225',
		url => 'http://www.lerner.co.il/',
		firstname => 'Reuven',
		lastname => 'Lerner');

$users{316709344} = \%one_user;
</pre>

<p>Now I can grab information:</p>

<pre>
print $users{316709344}->{email}, "\n";
</pre>

<p>Hashes in hashes are amazingly useful.  They're a fabulous data
structure, even if they are less space-efficient than arrays.</p>

<%attr>
title => 'Hashes in hashes'
</%attr>
